Credit Suisse Sets Limit on Bankers’ Bonus Reductions, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-25T02:33:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/credit-suisse-sets-limit-on-bankers-bonus-reductions-ft-says.html
Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  has limited
the reductions to bonuses paid to its senior bankers, which
would kick in if their businesses lost money, to 15 percent for
every 1 billion Swiss francs ($1.1 billion) of loss per
division, the Financial Times reported, citing the group’s
annual report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 